    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a collector-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a pristine example of 90s analog performance. This chassis retains its original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, with recent compression tests yielding optimal, uniform results across all rotor faces. The sequential transition remains seamless, delivering linear boost through the factory-spec intercooler piping. Power is managed via the original 5-speed short-throw manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential. The suspension geometry is untouched, featuring the factory aluminum double-wishbone setup that ensures a perfect 50/50 weight distribution. Free of aftermarket modifications, this vehicle represents a rare opportunity to own a mechanically synchronized, showroom-quality icon with zero thermal degradation or vacuum line fatigue.",
